Description

Central Marylebone luxury 1 bedroom apartment with modern decor designed with attention to every aspect of the high spec interior. Fully fitted kitchen with new appliances from Miele, Siemens and Smeg. Features a large private roof terrace and balcony from the front. This first floor apartment offers an ample reception room with high quality flooring throughout, brand new furniture, living room with sofas, TV and study/desk.

The property is just moments away from the shopping facilities of Oxford Street, Bond Street, Regents Street and the capital's finest Regents Park, Portman Square and Hyde Park. The nearest Tube Stations are Baker Street, Marylebone and Marble Arch, offering easy access to the City and all major London airports.

Water costs explained

Water consumption is based on average water usage for the predicted occupancy of the property based on the number of bedrooms.
Total annual consumption (in cubic meters) is then averaged into a monthly cost.
Note: If you have 2 separate suppliers for water and sewage, you may receive 2 separate bills.

Council tax explained

The Council Tax cost displayed is based on the council tax band and on the basis of 2 adults living at the property. The monthly cost shown excludes any discounts and is rounded to the nearest pound.
Full information on Council Tax discount entitlements can be found on the Gov.UK's website.
